    "updated_at": "2024-08-05T19:57:40Z",
    "body": "> One other thought @ekorchmar you had mentioned I should be using the $shell module, can you point me in the right direction of an example of that?\r\n\r\nConsidering the default config already places `$shell` module before the `$character`, you only need to enable it and (optionally) set indicators for shells you are using. So you could just remove the extra character from `success_symbol` declaration and add something like this to the end of the TOML:\r\n```toml\r\n[shell]\r\ndisabled = false\r\nbash_indicator = \"\"\r\nzsh_indicator = \"\"\r\npowershell_indicator = \"\"\r\nfish_indicator = \"󰈺\"\r\ncmd_indicator = \"\"\r\ntcsh_indicator = \"\"\r\n```\r\nThis would enable the same config to be shared among all shells with the desired effect of displaying the shell.\r\n\r\nThose are symbols from my config, but you can use any character or string in their place. All available indicators are listed in the [docs](https://starship.rs/config/#shell)",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "pin": null,
